18.71	My_Favorite_Husband	My Favorite Husband	My Favorite Husband is the name of an American radio program and network television series. The original radio show, co-starring Lucille Ball, was the initial basis for what evolved into the groundbreaking TV sitcom I Love Lucy. The series was based on the novels Mr. and Mrs. Cugat, the Record of a Happy Marriage (1940) and Outside Eden (1945) written by Isabel Scott Rorick, which had previously been adapted into the Paramount Pictures feature film Are Husbands Necessary? (1942), co-starring Ray Milland and Betty Field.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/34/Denninglucycolor.jpg/300px-Denninglucycolor.jpg
